==English==
===Etymology===
From [[endo-]] "inside" + [[thermic]] "of heat"
===Adjective===
'''endothermic'''

#{{chemistry}}: Of a [[chemical]] [[reaction]] that absorbs [[heat]] [[energy]] from its surroundings.
#{{zoology}}: Of an [[animal]] whose [[body]] [[temperature]] is regulated by [[internal]] factors.

===Antonym===
*[[exothermic]]

